docs.lead_paragraph: Two tons of decaying fruit, spoiled fish, and bad eggs were dumped at the foot of Rutgers Street yesterday, the result of a morning's raid by the officers of the Board of Health.

headline.main: RAIDING STREET STANDS; HEALTH BOARD INSPECTORS VISIT THE EAST SIDE. THEY SEIZE TONS OF DECAYED FRUIT, FISH, AND EGGS AND THROW THEM INTO THE RIVER -- PICTURESQUE INCIDENTS OF THE DESCENT INTO ESSEX STREET.
